commentTextItems.html: Warner skips back and punches this short ball from outside off past the covers. Australia seal a bonus-point win

commentPostTextItems.html: 6.30pm: Zampa and Lyon set up the victory, taking three wickets each, to dismiss West Indies for 116. Warner and Finch laid the platform for the chase with a 44-run opening stand. Khawaja flickered briefly and then Narine caused a middle-order wobble, but Warner completed his half-century and the chase.

Jason Holder: We din't bat well and there was no excuses. We din't put enough runs on the board. We lost wickets in clusters and we were not to build any partnerships. It was a bad batting display and we need to put this behind us. Seven soft dismissals and we need to spend some time in the wicket. I don't think the bowlers can be faulted.

Steven Smith: It would have been nice to keep it clinical. To get over the line with a bonus point, it is still pretty pleasing. Hopefully, we can keep building. The spinners were magnificent today. It may be the same surface against SA and they are licking their lips. Warner was calm and composed and got the team over the line. South Africa will be a challenge and I daresay it will be a battle of spinners, they will also play two spinners. The guys are coming off the IPL and it was nice to get this game out of the way with a bonus point.

Lyon, Man of the Match: I was pretty happy with the effort. To bowl WI out for 116 was a good effort. Zampa is a good mate and great to see him come along leaps and bounds. Great place to play cricket and it is going to be spin-friendly in the next game against South Africa.
That is all we have for you. Thanks for tuning in. Goodbye and cheers!

commentTextItems.html: keeps it short and outside off, Warner reaches out and chops to short third man
another half-tracker outside off, forces a cut past the covers off the back foot

commentPreTextItems.html: Narine has finished off. Fletcher. He bowls legspin

commentTextItems.html: half-tracker outside off, swatted on the back foot to midwicket
slides on middle, a touch short, the batsman keeps back and defends it back to Benn

commentTextItems.html: hint of turn away from the right hander, dabbed to backward point

Warner hangs back and chops a single to short third man. He sets off for a single. Marsh, however, isn't as quick as Warner. But he slides his bat in and makes it. A direct hit could have put him in trouble
turns just outside off, jabbed to the off side
Marsh stretches forward and meets a full toss. Paddled to fine leg for three. Positive running
full on off, Marsh flashes a drive to extra cover
big turn away from Warner. He pulls his bat inside the line and leaves it be

commentPostTextItems.html: vijay: "Warner's experience of playing on similar kind of pitches, similar kind of situations in IPL coming handy today.."

dismissalText.commentary: Andre Fletcher c Maxwell b Starc 4 (4b 1x4 0x6 6m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: gone. Whoa. Some start this. Full and wide outside off, not a lot of swing but enough. Fletcher wafts at it aimlessly and the skew flies to backward point. Comfortable height and comfortably taken. Starc has a wicket in his first over on international return

headshotImage.caption: Adam Zampa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adam Zampa player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Darren Bravo c Zampa b Marsh 19 (31b 3x4 0x6 46m) SR: 61.29

dismissalComment.html: poor shot. Full and wide, Bravo lays into a drive but fails to keep it down. Hits an uppish drive but straight to extra cover who juggles it and then takes it inches away from the ground. Not sure what he was trying to do there, maybe through the stroke too early

dismissalText.commentary: Johnson Charles b Starc 22 (40b 1x4 1x6 64m) SR: 55

dismissalComment.html: bowled im. That's why he was brought back. Charles' struggling innings ends. A superb yorker again, not for the first time Charles gets an inside edge but this time it rattled into middle stump. Late swing back in. Superb stuff from Starc

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels lbw b Lyon 10 (14b 0x4 0x6 28m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: given this time by umpire Brathwaite. Flat on middle and leg, skids on with the arm. The ball thuds into Samuels' pads in front of leg. This time the finger goes up. Samuels went deep in his crease but just missed his flick. Umpire's call at best/worst so a good decision not to review

headshotImage.caption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kieron Pollard c Warner b Lyon 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: straight to long-on. Pollard falls. Australia have two in two. Lyon has two in two. The same shot that got WI out of trouble in the previous game causes further misery for WI here. Tossed up on middle, some spin takes the inside half of Pollard's bat who looked to go down the ground with an uppish loft. That turn helped the ball lands straight in Warner's lap at long-on

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin lbw b Maxwell 12 (30b 0x4 0x6 40m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: an appeal for lbw, Maxi gets it to straighten, given! Pushed on middle, Ramdin presses forward and plays across the line and is trapped in front. Rapped on the front pad. No inside snick involved. Ump Brathwaite's call is vindicated. Ramdin's review amounts to nothing. The tracker shows it would hit middle. Maxi leaves the hosts six down

headshotImage.caption: Adam Zampa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adam Zampa player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jason Holder b Zampa 1 (6b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: bowled 'em! Holder rocks away outside leg and exposes all three stumps. Zampa takes aim and locks his target. He fires a slider and takes the off stump. The hosts are seven down

dismissalText.commentary: Sulieman Benn c & b Lyon 3 (7b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: Soft, soft dismissal. Khawaja pats Lyon on the head. Looped up on middle, may have stopped a touch on Benn. He has to check his push-drive, he ends up plopping it back to Lyon

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner not out 55 (55b 3x4 1x6 110m) SR: 100
Aaron Finch lbw b Holder 19 (30b 4x4 0x6 33m) SR: 63.33

dismissalComment.html: plumb in front! Full and straight, Finch shuffles across, trying to flick over midwicket but just plain misses a straight one. The umpire's finger was up quicker than I could say out. Easy decision, Finch doesn't bother reviewing.

dismissalComment.html: Benn gets Khawaja. Rather, Khawaja gives it away. Subdued celebrations. Drifts outside leg, sticks in the surface. Khawaja flicks early and spoons a catch to short midwicket

dismissalText.commentary: Steven Smith lbw b Narine 6 (10b 1x4 0x6 10m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: Narine returns and strikes! Umpire Llong's finger goes up. Was that doing too much? Looked so. Biting offbreak, tossed full, from Narine, Smith is deceived and is rapped on the front pad in line with the stumps. Perhaps, curling down leg. Smith has to go though. He could have review it. The tracker confirms that it was slipping down leg

seriesStandings.notes:
21.9 Points 21.9.1 Preliminary Matches In a competition with three or four Members with ODI status and with a final match or series, the home Board will institute a points system as follows: Win, with bonus point - 5
Win, without bonus point - 4
Tie or No Result - 2
Loss - 0 In the event of teams finishing on equal points, the right to play in the final match or series will be determined as follows:
  • The team with the most number of wins
  • If still equal, the team with the most number of wins over the other team(s) who are equal on points and have the same number of wins
  • If still equal, the team with the highest number of bonus points
  • If still equal, the team with the highest net run rate
In a match declared as no result, run rate is not applicable. 21.9.2 Net Run Rate A team's net run rate is calculated by deducting from the average runs per over scored by that team throughout the competition, the average runs per over scored against that team throughout the competition. In the event of a team being all out in less than its full quota of overs, the calculation of its net run rate shall be based on the full quota of overs to which it would have been entitled and not on the number of overs in which the team was dismissed. Only those matches where results are achieved will count for the purpose of net run rate calculations. Where a match is abandoned, but a result is achieved under Duckworth/Lewis, for net run rate purposes Team 1 will be accredited with Team 2's Par Score on abandonment off the same number of overs faced by Team 2. Where a match is concluded but with Duckworth/Lewis having been applied at an earlier point in the match, Team 1 will be accredited with 1 run less than the final Target Score for Team 2 off the total number of overs allocated to Team 2 to reach the target. 21.9.3 Bonus Points The team that achieves a run rate of 1.25 times that of the opposition shall be awarded one bonus point. A team's run rate will be calculated by reference to the runs scored in an innings divided by the number of overs faced. Refer Appendix 6. 21.9.4 Final Match or Series If no result is achieved in a final the match shall be declared drawn. In the event of a drawn final, the prize money will be shared equally between the two competing teams.
